name: Brendan Caldwell
bio: Brendan is a Electrical Engineering Major in the Systems track from Aiea. He is the Treasurer for the IEEE Student Branch. His favorite thing to do is binge watch scary movies.

name: Jason Chen
bio: Jason is a Senior at University of Hawaii at Manoa majoring in Electrical Engineering in the Electro-physics track. Jason's hobby is learning digital art and watching anime.

name: Alex Chen
bio: Alex Chen is a senior in Electrical Engineering attending University of Hawai'i at Manoa. He is currently working on a Weather box project in Team Apple. His hobbies are soccer and sleeping.

name: Josh Renzo Claudio
bio: Josh is a Senior in Electrical Engineering and is the current Lab Manager of the Smart Campus Energy Lab. He interests are in embedded systems and STEM outreach. In his free time,  he likes to play video games and binge watch shows on Netflix.

name: Kyle Daquioag
bio: Kyle is a junior in Mechanical Engineering at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. He currently interns for Hitachi Rail Honolulu JV in the project engineering department. His academic interests include 3D CAD design and automotives. Some of his hobbies involve basketball, weight lifting, and watching Netflix.

name: Aljaed Lui Ereno
bio: Aljaed Lui Ereno is a majoring in Computer Engineering at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. The first year of Aljaed's higher education was spent as a Computer Science major where he found out that, although he enjoyed the aspects of programming he was unsure if he specifically wanted to be in this path. His interests are broad but focused into the technology industry. As such, he is on the lookout for any opportunity to get experience in multiple disciplines to help identify what key niche/role he would dig deeper in. His first foray into the hardware world is through a project called SCEL, or Smart Campus Energy Lab, that is focused on developing a weather box that ideally would be used to gain weather data along with powering itself.  This project is also team based and therefore he also will be able to gain valuable insight into effective communication. In terms of software he has participated in another project called Microbotics where he joined the team whose primary role is to utilize the toolboxes in the application Matlab to do image processing on videos.

name: Keoni Inaba
bio: His name is Keoni. He stands at 5'6 and weighs 160 lbs. He majors in electrical engineering at the University of Hawaii. He is currently a sophomore. His academic goals are to graduate college and make his mother proud. He also plays the basketball from time to time and cooks for his friends and family.

name: Noah Ines
bio: Noah Ines is currently a Junior studying at the University of Hawai'i at Manoa. He intends to finish a Bachelors Degree in Electrical Engineering. In his downtime, he enjoys going running and watching anime.

name: Mikel Ishihara
bio: Mikel Ishihara is a sophomore in computer engineering. His hobbies include going to the gym and anime.

name: Sharmaine Javier
bio: Sharmaine is currently a junior in Electrical Engineering, Electro-Physics track at UH Manoa. Her interests include hardware and PCB design. During her free time, she listens to music or watch dramas.

name: Anthony Kuh
bio: Anthony Kuh received the B.S degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from the University of California, Berkeley. He continued to obtain his M.S. in Electrical Engineering from Stanford University. He later obtained his Ph.D in Electrical Engineering from Princeton University. He is currently a Professor for the Electrical Engineering Department at the University of Hawaii at Manoa.

name: Alicia Leong
bio: Alicia Leong is currently a Senior attending the University of Hawaii at Manoa with a major in computer engineering. Her main academic interest are in embedded systems and the internet of things. Her goals after graduation is to find a job on the mainland. During her free time she enjoys reading and spending time with her friends.

name: Diwen Lin
bio: Diwen Lin is currently a Junior at UH Manoa studying Electrical Engineering, Diwen's academic goal is to maintain a minimum of 3.90 GPA by the end of his college career. His interests are MOBA games, math, reading Chinese novels, and renewable energy.

name: Kylie Lin
bio: Kylie Lin is a senior in computer engineering at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. She is part of the SCEL Firmware Team. Her academic interest include web application. Hobbies include tennis, light reading, and watching traditional Chinese dramas.

name: Mizpah Mansanao
bio: Mizpah Mansanao is a senior in Electrical Engineering in the Electro-physics track. Her interests involve building circuits and not getting burn when soldering. Mizpah's hobbies include going to the gym, thrift shopping and watching/making vlogs. She enjoys laughing with her SCEL lab mates and hopes to be the next Ms. Universe.

name: Max Mochizuki
bio: Max is currently a junior at the University of Hawaii at Manoa, majoring in Electrical Engineering. He was born and raised on the island of Maui and graduated high school with 44 college credits. In his free time, Max enjoys watching Netflix, working out, or catching the sunset.

name: Allen John Namoca
bio: Allen Namoca's interests include Digital Art and Video Games. Other interests include Website Designs and Problem Solving (regarding coding and mystery scenarios).

name: Jianna Leonora Orias
bio: Jianna is currently a senior who will be taking an extra semester to obtain more experience in Computer Engineering and Science (expected graduation: Fall 2020). Currently, she is the President of the Engineers' Council at the University of Hawaii and is trying to keep everything flowing smoothly. For the Fall 2019 Semester, she is also interning with amazing people at ICX Transportation Group. She has aspirations to get peace of mind and maybe a bartending license on the side (and maybe even mix programming and bartending somehow). Please wish her the best of luck as she needs it very much this whole year.

name: Thomas Pekelo
bio: Thomas Pekelo is a junior in Electrical Engineering at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. His academic interests include programming and circuit design. His hobbies include fishing and hiking.

name: Alana Power
bio: Alana Power is a Junior majoring in Electrical Engineering, Electrophysics track. She is on the Firmware team focusing on the utilization of a Raspberry Pi as a test platform. Her academic interests include programming, hardware, and mathematics. In her free time, she enjoys watching movies, doing art, and crocheting. After graduating, Alana would like to find an engineering job somewhere on the mainland.

name: Andrew Salazar
bio: Andrew Salazar is a junior at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. His major is computer engineering and he is expected to graduate in Spring 2021. The activities he enjoys are video games, archery, meme-making, and sleeping. He has an interest in game development, front-end and back-end programming, and PC building.

name: Rammell Transfiguracion
bio: Rammell Transfiguracion is an Electrical Engineering major focused on the electro-physics track at the University of Hawaii at Manoa.  He is now the senior member in Smart Campus Energy Lab's Weather Box Team Guava.  As part of a 3 member team; focused on developing a sensor node module to collect meteorological data for the future implementation of renewable energy sources. This semester, the goal is to properly deploy Team Guava's Weather Box successfully.

name: Kylie Urasaki
bio: Kylie is a sophomore pursuing Electrical Engineering, Electro-Physics track at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. Her academic goals are to learn more about Electrical Engineering as a whole and more specifically, renewable energy. In her free time, she enjoys playing trombone and playing Pokmon Go.

name: Raellis Young
bio: Raellis Young is a Junior majoring in Electrical Engineering at the College of Engineering, Systems track. Her academic goals are to learn more about electrical circuits and how to apply this knowledge for renewable energy. During her free time she enjoys hiking, hanging out with friends, listening to music and watching dramas outside of school.
